The [[Metric topology]] of the [[Uniform metric]] on $$\mathbb{R}^J$$, for arbitrary [[Index set]] $$J$$

[[vid|https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=RFwtRWp2cBI&index=6&list=PLLq_gUfXAnkl8bjQh-hGQ9u24xZP9x0dx#t=1h7m11s]]

One of the [[three topologies in this space|https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=RFwtRWp2cBI&index=6&list=PLLq_gUfXAnkl8bjQh-hGQ9u24xZP9x0dx#t=1h7m49s]]

[[The uniform topology is finer than the |https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=RFwtRWp2cBI&index=6&list=PLLq_gUfXAnkl8bjQh-hGQ9u24xZP9x0dx#t=1h9m10s]] [[Product topology]], and strictly finer if J is infinite. It is also coarser than the [[Box topology]]. [[proof|https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=RFwtRWp2cBI&index=6&list=PLLq_gUfXAnkl8bjQh-hGQ9u24xZP9x0dx#t=1h15m30s]]. [[proof of strictly finer|https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=RFwtRWp2cBI&index=6&list=PLLq_gUfXAnkl8bjQh-hGQ9u24xZP9x0dx#t=1h29m24s]]